<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4951948>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 12. Pherusa papillata (Johnson, 1901). A. Syntypes (MCZ 1900), dorsal view. B. Same, anterior fragment, anterior end, dorsal view. C. Same, anterior end, ventral view (branchiae and palps exposed). D. Non-type specimen (USNM 43821), head, frontal view (branchiae and palps removed; BS: branchial scar, NL: nephridial lobe, PS: palp scar). E. Same, chaetiger 9, right parapodium, neurochaetae. F. Same, chaetiger 25, right parapodium, posterior view (insets: basal and distal notochaetal regions, largest neurohook). Scale bars: A: 3.3 mm, B: 1.5 mm, C: 0.9 mm, D: 0.4 mm, E: 0.1 mm, F: 0.3 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4951948/files/figure.png" .

